<br>
If there was an exploit possible, then fix the content of the zone being exploited. (I.E. put an invisible one-way wall up to prevent Gfluxing to a particular location)  I am getting tired of seeing all of our spells change everytime new content is introduced to the game.<br>
<br>
The quest to obtain Concussion has a harsh bottleneck with the Human Skeleton in CoM.  It is bad enough we need the help of a class with charm to do it, but without the ability to &quot;leap&quot; to the second floor via Gflux, this part of the quest will require even more assistance from others to be completed.  Concussion is a class defining ability for Wizards.  In my opinion it is our one great &quot;debuff&quot; line.  I used Gflux when I did the quest, and I feel sorry for those that won't be able to have this experience.  Utilizing all of the powers available to the Wizard class is what I consider the mark of a good player.<br>
<br>
I hate the idea that quests and encounters need to be designed in the game in such a way that there is only ONE WAY to succeed in them.  Nerfing the tools available to the player base to limit possible strategies is short sighted and bound to piss people off.<br>
<br>
/finger  to Gflux change.  The spell's only useful side was the &quot;flux&quot;...it was never the damage, AoE range, mana efficiency, etc.  It had a cool effect.  Stop fucking with our spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andraelarcaneumrunner>Andrael Arcaneumrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Hand Of<BR>The Cabal (tm)!!!</span><br>  Posts: 1834<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/14/03 10:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: STEALTH NERF #1!!!  Huge slap in the face to Wiz and Enc</span><hr size=1> Tell us how you REALLY feel.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daeanorendarion>Daeanor Endarion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 985<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/14/03 10:11 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: STEALTH NERF #1!!!  Huge slap in the face to Wiz and Enc</span><hr size=1> This change had nothing to do with exploits or how players use the spell. It was becasue every now and then, when <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>mobs</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cast it, a person would get 20k'd from the falling damage. I thought they were just removing the falling damage, but they killed the fly-up instead...kind of like fixing the leak in the fish tank by taking out the water.<br>
